'''Nicholas Brooks''' (born 20 May 1964) is a British visual effects artist. He won at the [[71st Academy Awards]] in the category of [[Academy Award for Best Visual Effects|Best Visual Effects]] for his work on ''[[What Dreams May Come (film)|What Dreams May Come]]''. He shared his Oscar with [[Joel Hynek]], [[Kevin Mack (visual effects artist)|Kevin Mack]] and [[Stuart Robertson (special effects artist)|Stuart Robertson]].<ref name="Oscars1999">{{Cite news |url= http://www.oscars.org/awards/academyawards/legacy/ceremony/71st-winners.html |title=The 71st Academy Awards (1999) Nominees and Winners |accessdate=April 25, 2014|work=[[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]]|publisher=AMPAS}}</ref>

He also won an [[Emmy Award]] for the special effects of the TV film ''[[Dreamkeeper]]''.

